      "reviews": [
        {
          "reviewTitle": "Great foundation",
          "reviewText": "I have used this foundation for years. I no longer have acne issues but I have yet to find a better foundation.",
          "reviewDate": "Reviewed in the United States on February 12, 2026",
          "customer": "Amazon Customer",
          "customerProfileUrl": "https://www.amazon.com/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AHG7SVR5JR5BXYD2M754PBKPUABQ",
          "customerStarsRating": 5,
          "productSpecs": {
            "color": "AK Neutral CN 52"
          }
        },
        {
          "reviewTitle": "Perfect Foundation for Sensitive Skin",
          "reviewText": "I don't often write reviews, but this foundation is worth it. I have extremely sensitive skin prone to acne. I have spent a lifetime never wearing any makeup on my face because, even wearing it for a rare special occasion, would make my face breakout for weeks. I decided to try this foundation on a whim for a special occasion, and what a difference. I still occasionally get a pimple if I wear it on a hot, sweaty day, but most of the time, my skin is clear. It took me a few tries to find my perfect match. I have light skin with red undertones. The match that worked best for me is AC Alabaster CN 10. I tried Flax, Ivory, and Cream Chamois. The Alabaster matches my skin naturally. I understand that skin is unique, and what works wonders for me, may not work on someone else's skin. That said, I highly recommend this foundation for anyone who struggles with sensitive, acne-prone skin. If it works, it's absolutely worth it. If it doesn't, your search continues...",
          "reviewDate": "Reviewed in the United States on November 4, 2025",
